OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA mainly dry and partly cloudy
OL,6,Fmorning. Sunny intervals and showers
OL,7,Ffor the afternoon, perhaps heavy with
OL,8,Fthe odd rumble of thunder. The best of
OL,9,Fthe dry and sunniest conditions on the
OL,10,Feast coast.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FShowers will gradually die
OL,13,Fout this evening. Turning cloudier
OL,14,Fthrough the early hours, with rain
OL,15,Fspreading in from the west towards the
OL,16,Fend of the night.
OL,17,
OL,18,CTuesday:FAn overcast and wet morning,
OL,19,Fthe rain occasionally heavy. Brighter
OL,20,Fspells and showers developing for the
OL,21,Fafternoon, some likely heavy at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
